  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some things new employees should know going into their first day at First Potomac Realty?",
  "response": "Welcome to First Potomac Realty! Starting a new job can be both exciting and a bit daunting, but with the right information, you'll feel more confident and prepared. Here are several things new employees should know going into their first day:\n\n1. **Company Overview**: First Potomac Realty is a real estate investment trust (REIT) focused on owning, operating, and developing office and industrial properties in the Washington, D.C. metropolitan area.\n\n2. **Dress Code**: Understand the dress code for your role, whether it's business casual, business formal, or something else. It's usually better to dress more formally on the first day.\n\n3. **Office Location and Hours**: Know the address of the office, parking details if you drive, public transportation options if relevant, and office hours. Aim to arrive a little early.\n\n4. **Onboarding Process**: You will likely go through an orientation session or onboarding process where you\u2019ll learn about company policies, procedures, and culture. Bring necessary identification for paperwork.\n\n5. **Direct Supervisor**: Know who your direct supervisor is, as well as any colleagues you\u2019ll be working closely with. This will help you know whom to approach with questions and concerns.\n\n6. **Key Contacts**: Get familiar with the HR representative or department, IT support, and any other key contacts who could assist you with initial issues (computer setup, access to systems, etc.).\n\n7. **Company Culture and Values**: Familiarize yourself with the organizational culture and core values. Understanding these can help you integrate better and align your work with the company\u2019s goals.\n\n8. **Tools and Systems**: Be prepared to learn various software systems and tools that the company uses for daily operations. You might want to review any materials provided ahead of time.\n\n9. **Communication Channels**: Find out the preferred methods of communication within the office, whether it\u2019s email, messaging apps, or face-to-face meetings.\n\n10. **Expectations and Goals**: Understand your job responsibilities and any immediate tasks or projects you might be expected to start working on. Clarity on expectations can help you prioritize and manage your time effectively.\n\n11. **Office Norms**: Understand the office norms, including break times, lunch routines, and the availability of amenities like a cafeteria, kitchen, or coffee machines.\n\n12. **Social Integration**: Don\u2019t hesitate to introduce yourself to colleagues and participate in team activities or informal gatherings. Building professional relationships early on can enhance your experience.\n\n13. **Questions and Support**: It\u2019s completely natural to have questions on your first day. Don\u2019t hesitate to ask for help or clarification\u2014your colleagues and supervisors are usually happy to assist new team members.\n\nPreparation is key, so take some time before your first day to review any material provided by HR or your supervisor. This proactive approach will help ease your transition into the company. All the best at First Potomac Realty!",
